The author recounts his experiences as a senior golfer with modest ability and great enthusiasm, relating humorous anecdotes and personal glimpses from his 60 years of so-called lousy golf. Description: IW Health develops and deploys a customized prescription adherence platform to provide solutions for patients with chronic illness.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: IW Health develops and deploys a prescription compliance solution platform to combat medication non-compliance. By reducing non-compliance we significantly decrease the healthcare costs for health insurers and employers, also enhancing the revenue for retail pharmacies and pharmaceutical companies.  We deliver our reminder solution Rx Tracker, to persons taking daily, weekly or monthly medications, via text message, email or Interactive Voice Response call to a land line phone. Once the patient receives the medication reminder, they are prompted to respond with a compliance acknowledgement, this data is then stored on the Rx Tracker web application and the patients electronic health record. The patient can opt-in their doctors, family members or friends to view their healthcare information.  The second component of Rx Tracker is the ability to track a prescription, remind the patient of an approaching need for a refill and offers a refill authorization right from their phone.    The key to Rx Tracker's success is the data generated from the reminder components of the system, this data leads patients to better health outcomes and more cost-effective choices for both them and their healthcare partners (retail pharmacies, doctors and health insurer). In short by reducing medication non-compliance we: Significantly reduce direct healthcare costs Reduce or eliminate costly emergency room visits and unneeded hospitalizations and in some cases save patients lives.
Industry Groups: Health Care, Internet Services, Messaging and Telecommunications, Mobile

Hours: Mon-Sun - 10am-6pm Payment: All cc Description: Russian business visas allow for a single, double or multiple visits and may be valid from one to twelve months. While tourist visa cannot be extended, business visa extensions can be arranged through the organisation which provided the invitation for the existing business visa.   Please note that a multiple entry visa is only available for people who have been issued a Russian visa before. A copy of your previous visa should be enclosed to your new application. If this visa was processed before 2013, we strongly recommend that you should contact your local Russian consulate and make sure that a multiple entry visa would still be available.   What are passport requirements for Russian visa? You have to submit your original passport with at least 2 blank visa-designated pages (passport must be valid for at least 6 months after intended departure date from Russia).   Foreign citizen minors must have a power-of-attorney, allowing them to travel if they are travelling alone or in the company of adults who are not their parents. Such miniors will be prevented from entering or leaving Russia if they cannot present such a power-of-attorney. In an effort to prevent international child abduction, many goverments have initiated special procedures at entry/exit points. These often include requiring documentary evidence of relationship and permission for the child's travel from the parent(s) or legal guardian if not present. Having such documentation on hand, even if not legally required, may facilitate entry/departure.

Description: The TBI facilitates scientific research in the Lake Turkana Basin in northern Kenya by providing researchers with logistical support.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: The Turkana Basin Institute (TBI) is a research institution that facilitates scientific research in the Lake Turkana Basin in northern Kenya by providing researchers with logistical support. It is a privately funded, non-profit initiative that researches about the time of the dinosaurs and crocodiles, time of the early primates, time of human origins, path to modern humans, and new scientific frontiers. The institute’s research facilities include TBI-Ileret: a facility situated about five kilometers from Ileret village, close to the Kenya-Ethiopia border on the east side of Lake Turkana; and TBI-Turkwel,a facility situated on the west side of Lake Turkana, near Nakechichok on the Turkwel River. The TBI works with Stony Brook University, the University College London, American University, and University of Helsinki. The Turkana Basin Institute was founded by Richard Leakey and Stony Brook University in 2005 and its operations are based in New York, United States and Nairobi, Kenya.
